  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Thursday. Today is Mom and Dad's wedding anniversary, and every year on this date, they retell the story of how they met, with small new details added each time.",
      "zh": "星期四。今天是媽媽和爸爸的結婚紀念日，每年到了這一天，他們都會重講一次相遇的故事，而且每次都會多加一些新細節。"
    },
    {
      "en": "According to Dad, he was a humble, low-level clerk at a small company, filing papers nobody else wanted to touch.",
      "zh": "根據爸爸的說法，他當時只是一位謙遜的低階職員，在一間小公司負責整理沒有人想碰的文件。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom, meanwhile, was a curious young woman visiting that same office to deliver a package for her own boss, who was too busy to go herself.",
      "zh": "同時，媽媽當時是一位好奇心旺盛的年輕女子，她去那間辦公室送一個包裹，是幫她自己的主管跑腿，因為主管太忙不能親自去。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I accidentally called her by the wrong name,\" Dad admitted, \"which, looking back, was an extremely rude way to start a conversation.\"",
      "zh": "「我不小心叫錯了她的名字，」爸爸坦承：「現在回想起來，這實在是個很沒禮貌的開場方式。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom laughed and said she was too shy at the time to correct him properly, so she just quietly answered to the wrong name for ten whole minutes.",
      "zh": "媽媽笑著說，她當時太害羞，不好意思糾正他，所以就安安靜靜地答應了整整十分鐘那個叫錯的名字。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"He seemed like such a gentleman otherwise,\" she said, \"clumsy, but genuinely kind, which honestly matters more in the long run.\"",
      "zh": "「除此之外他看起來還滿紳士的，」她說：「笨手笨腳，但真心善良，長遠來看，這其實更重要。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "They ran into each other again a few weeks later, and this time Dad remembered her actual name, calling it \"a small but important step forward.\"",
      "zh": "幾個星期後他們又碰面了，這次爸爸記住了她真正的名字，他說這是「一個雖小但很重要的進步」。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia, who has heard this story roughly one hundred times, still pretends to be surprised at the exact same part every single year.",
      "zh": "Sophia 已經聽過這個故事大概一百次了，每年還是假裝在同一個橋段感到驚訝。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Marriage takes more than one lucky meeting,\" she added, cutting into the anniversary cake with unusual precision. \"It takes years of choosing each other, again and again.\"",
      "zh": "「婚姻靠的不只是一次幸運的相遇，」她一邊補充，一邊異常精準地切著紀念蛋糕：「靠的是一年又一年、一次又一次選擇彼此。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "William asked what a husband and a wife actually promise each other, and Dad said, simply, to stay kind on the difficult days, not just the easy ones.",
      "zh": "William 問丈夫和妻子到底彼此承諾了什麼，爸爸簡單地說：在困難的日子裡也要保持善良，不只是在輕鬆的日子裡。"
    },
    {
      "en": "This year's dinner also included my aunt and uncle, along with their two kids, meaning I officially have one more nephew and one niece to keep track of.",
      "zh": "今年的晚餐還多了我阿姨和姨丈，加上他們兩個孩子，代表我現在多了一位姪子和一位姪女要記得。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My little niece kept asking Mom to retell the \"wrong name\" part over and over, clearly the most popular scene in the entire family legend.",
      "zh": "我的小姪女一直要求媽媽把「叫錯名字」那段一講再講，顯然這是整個家族傳說裡最受歡迎的一幕。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My nephew, older and far more mature than William, mostly just wanted extra cake, which is honestly a very mature goal to have.",
      "zh": "我的姪子年紀比較大，也比 William 成熟很多，他大部分時候只想多要一塊蛋糕，老實說，這也算是個滿成熟的目標。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the end of dinner, Mom and Dad had told the story exactly the same way they always do, wrong name, rude first impression, and all.",
      "zh": "晚餐結束時，媽媽和爸爸還是照著他們一貫的方式講完了整個故事，叫錯名字、無禮的第一印象，全部一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: apparently the secret to a good marriage is one accidental wrong name, a lot of patience, and repeating the same story every single year with a smile.",
      "zh": "今日心得：顯然一段好婚姻的秘訣，就是一次意外叫錯的名字、大量的耐心，還有每年都帶著笑容重講同一個故事。"
    }
  ],
